gmdn_terms.name: Surgical retractor/retraction system blade, reusable
gmdn_terms.definition: A distal component of a surgical retraction system, surgical retractor, and/or surgical instrument assist arm system designed to function as a parting edge to separate the margins of a wound/incision during a surgical procedure. It is intended to be attached to the frame (e.g., mounting ring/bar) of a surgical retraction system, or may be fixed onto a retractor handle; it does not include a handle. It is a metal device, sometimes referred to as a variable or vario retractor blade when assembled with a separate retractor handle, because it is available in a variety of lengths and sizes. This is a reusable device.

gmdn_terms.name: Cardiac/peripheral vascular guidewire, single-use

It is used for various diagnostic and interventional procedures, and may include devices used to facilitate manipulation (e.g., torque device). This is a single-use device.

gmdn_terms.definition: An implantable device designed to replace one or more vertebral body(s) that has collapsed or been surgically removed due to trauma, tumour or degenerative disease.
